The paper is about developing a new approach to train a Variational Autoencoder (VAE) in non-Euclidean spaces with constant curvature. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given that the paper focuses on developing a new method for training VAEs, which is a popular technique in machine learning, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG.
